Description: A natural undyed fragment of a fine quality, wool textile used as a wrapping. The weave is plain and weft-face. The spinning direction of the warp yarn is zz/s-ply and the weft yarn is single s-twist. The thread count is warp 7 per 10mm and weft 25 per 10mm. Large holes are present. A short cord is attached to the larger fragment. Its direction of spinning is sss/z-ply.
Curator's comments: A short cord is attached to the larger fragment. Its direction of spinning is sss/z-ply. This may be a twist of warp yarns from production of the fabric.
Bibliographic references: Adams et al 1999 / Kulubnarti III: The Cemeteries (p. 60, 65)
